WEBVTT

00:00.067 --> 00:03.836
♪♪

00:07.408 --> 00:11.043
♪♪

00:14.949 --> 00:18.984
♪♪

00:22.422 --> 00:26.925
♪♪

00:29.964 --> 00:32.030
Come on.

00:32.032 --> 00:33.231
Mama, it's fine.

00:33.233 --> 00:36.969
It's fine when
I say it's fine, okay?

00:36.971 --> 00:38.370
Look, you even scuffed
up the shoes.

00:38.372 --> 00:39.772
Go on, take 'em off.
Let me shine them.

00:39.774 --> 00:42.174
It's just dust.
Look.

00:42.176 --> 00:43.442
See?
-Hurry up now.

00:43.444 --> 00:44.909
You're gonna be late.

00:44.911 --> 00:46.378
Who needs school anyway?

00:46.380 --> 00:48.781
You do.

00:48.783 --> 00:50.515
You're not a loser
like the rest of them.

00:50.517 --> 00:52.317
You different than that!

00:52.319 --> 00:56.855
Yeah, well, I don't want
to be different.

00:56.857 --> 01:01.259
I just want to be normal
like everybody else.

01:01.261 --> 01:02.461
Just like you.

01:02.463 --> 01:04.262
All right, go on now.

01:04.264 --> 01:06.465
Fix your sweater.
Have a good day.

01:06.467 --> 01:08.267
You too.

01:08.935 --> 01:11.637
♪♪

01:16.343 --> 01:18.677
♪♪

01:23.350 --> 01:27.519
♪♪

01:32.893 --> 01:35.995
♪♪

01:40.835 --> 01:43.235
♪♪

01:46.907 --> 01:48.507
You gonna ask your mom?

01:48.509 --> 01:49.774
Oh, yeah, right.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.643
Yeah, that'll go well.

01:51.645 --> 01:53.846
[ Laughs ]
Well, just ask her really nice.

01:53.848 --> 01:55.313
You never get to
go anywhere.

01:55.315 --> 01:58.116
Boy, your mama keeps you
on a short leash.

01:58.118 --> 02:00.785
Well, yeah, she just hates
being alone.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.454
That's just
how she is.

02:02.456 --> 02:04.122
What do you think
of Miss Mina's quiz?

02:04.124 --> 02:07.792
-I can't stand her.
-Well, she is from Alabama.

02:07.794 --> 02:11.396
Girl, you look sweet enough
to put on my cornflakes.

02:11.398 --> 02:12.865
Mm!

02:12.867 --> 02:14.666
Students:
I pledge allegiance to the Flag

02:14.668 --> 02:16.735
of the United States of America,

02:16.737 --> 02:20.205
and to the Republic
for which it stands,

02:20.207 --> 02:23.542
one nation under God,
indivisible,

02:23.544 --> 02:26.045
with liberty
and justice for all.

02:28.883 --> 02:31.216
Teacher: Today we're going to
look at six main factors

02:31.218 --> 02:34.018
that caused
the Industrial Revolution --

02:34.020 --> 02:38.022
the rail system, steam power,
coal extraction,

02:38.024 --> 02:39.357
iron smelting...

02:39.359 --> 02:42.895
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:50.304 --> 02:53.438
Can I sit here?

02:53.440 --> 02:55.373
You can sit
wherever you like.

02:55.375 --> 02:56.708
-Well, I'm new here --
-Oh, God.

02:56.710 --> 02:58.243
Mary Lou,
don't sit here.

02:58.245 --> 03:01.547
That's a Negro table.
Come sit with us.

03:05.252 --> 03:08.887
Well, I've never seen one
with that green of eyes before.

03:12.927 --> 03:15.060
What'd you get?

03:15.062 --> 03:16.395
Tater tots.

03:16.997 --> 03:19.231
♪♪

03:22.136 --> 03:24.269
Hey, be careful out here,
Snow White.

03:24.271 --> 03:25.270
You're gonna catch fire.

03:25.272 --> 03:27.005
Burning my eyes, hodad.

03:27.007 --> 03:30.208
Has he ever walked
on a beach before?

03:30.210 --> 03:32.044
Nice socks!

03:33.013 --> 03:35.447
♪♪

03:41.488 --> 03:45.257
♪♪

03:47.762 --> 03:50.562
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:52.833 --> 03:55.434
Women in cages
is gonna be amazing, baby.

03:55.436 --> 03:57.970
It's gonna be fantastic.
-I know it will.

03:58.572 --> 04:01.106
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

04:04.979 --> 04:06.444
Hey! Fella!

04:06.446 --> 04:08.313
What are you doing?

04:08.315 --> 04:09.982
Gerry! Gerry!

04:12.252 --> 04:14.186
Hey!

04:14.188 --> 04:15.854
Come back here!
What are you doing?

04:15.856 --> 04:17.722
Come back here!

04:17.724 --> 04:19.057
Hey!

04:19.059 --> 04:20.793
-Who the hell is that guy?
-Get him.

04:20.795 --> 04:22.394
Son of a bitch!

04:22.396 --> 04:24.196
Asshole!
You're an asshole!

04:24.198 --> 04:25.798
Get back --

04:25.800 --> 04:27.732
[ Panting ]

04:27.734 --> 04:29.868
You'll ruin me!
You'll ruin me!

04:29.870 --> 04:32.270
You ruined yourself,
sweetheart.

04:32.272 --> 04:33.538
Come on!

04:33.540 --> 04:36.608
[ Crying ]

04:36.610 --> 04:41.413
Why? No! Please!
No, please!

04:41.415 --> 04:44.416
Who are you?
Please.

04:44.418 --> 04:47.352
I'm nobody, but you...

04:47.354 --> 04:49.755
-Come back here!
-You wanted to be famous.

04:53.494 --> 04:55.828
[ Laughter ]

04:55.830 --> 04:57.629
Brinda: Them the new Mary Janes
with the T-strap?

04:57.631 --> 04:59.297
Oh, yeah,
Mama got them.

04:59.299 --> 05:01.166
I had to wear something
to make me smile today,

05:01.168 --> 05:02.967
what with that quiz
Miss Comiskey gave and all.

05:02.969 --> 05:04.837
Ain't she a nasty old cow,
though?

05:04.839 --> 05:06.505
Yeah.

05:06.507 --> 05:09.508
[ Radio playing indistinctly ]

05:09.510 --> 05:14.046
♪♪

05:14.048 --> 05:15.848
Sharon: What you smiling at,
girl?

05:15.850 --> 05:19.251
What the hell
you smiling at?

05:19.253 --> 05:21.520
You been spending time
with Lewis?

05:21.522 --> 05:22.655
That's what it is?

05:22.657 --> 05:24.122
Oh,
so that's your man now?

05:24.124 --> 05:25.590
Well, yeah, we've been
spending some time --

05:25.592 --> 05:28.527
Bitch, he ain't.
You ain't even...

05:28.529 --> 05:31.329
Light-skinned bitch think
you all that, and you ain't.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.198
I'ma see if that light skin
scratch off.

05:33.200 --> 05:34.667
I'ma see if
that blood is black.

05:34.669 --> 05:36.401
Oh, screw you, Sharon,
you coconut.

05:36.403 --> 05:38.336
Take it up with Lewis
where he spends his time.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.004
I'ma see if that blood
is black.

05:40.006 --> 05:42.607
Come on, Sharon.
She ain't doing nothing.

05:42.609 --> 05:44.943
Just let it go, girl.

05:44.945 --> 05:46.411
Don't go crying, baby.

05:46.413 --> 05:48.813
You gon' fink
to your mama?

05:48.815 --> 05:50.014
[ Laughs ]

05:50.016 --> 05:52.150
Pat,
you know what she like.

05:52.152 --> 05:54.853
She's always been
so boy crazy.

05:58.358 --> 05:59.691
Look.

05:59.693 --> 06:01.994
Yeah, I see.
That's him.

06:04.231 --> 06:06.831
Yeah, I told you.
He never stays long.

06:06.833 --> 06:11.236
Just looking,
a couple minutes.

06:11.238 --> 06:14.707
Snap case.
Why he looking at you?

06:14.709 --> 06:16.709
I don't know.
I didn't do nothing.

06:16.711 --> 06:19.644
Shit,
you done something.

06:19.646 --> 06:21.045
I got to go.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.581
-Bye, girl.
-See ya.

06:22.583 --> 06:25.317
[ Engine starts ]

06:25.319 --> 06:29.121
♪♪

06:29.123 --> 06:30.388
Yeah, th-they were right there,

06:30.390 --> 06:32.791
right wh-wh-where
you said they'd be.

06:32.793 --> 06:34.859
Salazaar:<i> That's great, kid.</i>
<i> I mean, that was a smart play,</i>

06:34.861 --> 06:36.661
<i> coming back from the beach,</i>
<i> huh?</i>

06:36.663 --> 06:37.730
[<i> Chuckles</i> ]

06:37.732 --> 06:41.400
<i> She'll be back in Iowa</i>
<i> in 24 hours.</i>

06:41.402 --> 06:43.001
<i> Jay?</i>

06:43.003 --> 06:44.937
<i> Jay, you there?</i>
-Yeah.

06:44.939 --> 06:46.538
<i> Bring 'em in now,</i>
<i> why don't you?</i>

06:46.540 --> 06:48.140
<i> You know, if they're good,</i>
<i> that's a grand easy</i>

06:48.142 --> 06:49.942
<i> and see what the run</i>
<i> ends up being.</i>

06:49.944 --> 06:54.212
<i> I mean, if I break a hundred,</i>
<i> you'll see it, I promise.</i>

06:54.214 --> 06:56.615
I, ah...

06:56.617 --> 06:59.884
I-I didn't get them.

06:59.886 --> 07:02.020
<i> What?</i>
<i> What did you say?</i>

07:02.022 --> 07:04.356
<i> Sorry, Jay, it sounded like</i>
<i> you said you didn't get them.</i>

07:04.358 --> 07:06.491
Uh, yeah, I did-- I did--
I didn't get them.

07:06.493 --> 07:09.894
I didn't get the shots.
The, uh -- The, uh --

07:09.896 --> 07:11.764
The camera got smashed.

07:11.766 --> 07:14.767
<i> You stupid son of a bitch!</i>

07:14.769 --> 07:16.434
<i> You clown.</i>

07:16.436 --> 07:20.439
<i> You -- You get a new camera,</i>
<i> you go back there, idiot.</i>

07:20.441 --> 07:22.174
<i> You stupid son of a bitch!</i>
<i> What have you done?</i>

07:22.176 --> 07:23.908
Sal. Sal! Shut up!
Shut up.

07:23.910 --> 07:26.044
Just shut up.
Shut up.

07:26.046 --> 07:28.647
I got the pictures.
I was kidding.

07:28.649 --> 07:30.449
I'm bringing them in.
Here I come.

07:30.451 --> 07:32.184
I was kidding.

07:41.328 --> 07:44.530
♪♪

07:46.600 --> 07:48.000
[ Sniffs ]

07:50.270 --> 07:51.536
[ Keys jingling ]

07:51.538 --> 07:54.006
[ Sighs ]

07:54.008 --> 07:57.376
[ Sniffs sharply, coughs ]

07:59.946 --> 08:03.582
♪♪

08:06.887 --> 08:09.954
♪♪

08:09.956 --> 08:13.225
[ Engine starts ]

08:13.828 --> 08:16.829
♪♪

08:18.699 --> 08:22.167
♪♪

08:24.304 --> 08:26.972
Pat! Psst.

08:29.176 --> 08:31.376
Sorry for
spottin' your floor.

08:31.378 --> 08:34.246
-That's all right.
-Why'd you light out so quick?

08:34.248 --> 08:35.848
I would've
walked with you.

08:35.850 --> 08:38.217
I didn't want to be late.

08:40.855 --> 08:43.121
You're gonna
get us both fired.

08:43.123 --> 08:45.790
Sister Sarah's watching.
-Oh, poo Sister Sarah.

08:45.792 --> 08:49.461
You knockin' off at 7:00?
I'll walk you home.

08:49.463 --> 08:51.730
Yeah.
Don't let my mama see.

08:51.732 --> 08:55.133
Your mama is
a whole different story.

08:55.135 --> 08:56.502
I'll see you at 7:00.

09:02.609 --> 09:03.942
My cousin's got
a good job for me

09:03.944 --> 09:06.945
over at the auto shop
on Centinela.

09:06.947 --> 09:07.946
Full time.

09:07.948 --> 09:10.482
You gonna drop out?

09:10.484 --> 09:11.483
Maybe.

09:11.485 --> 09:14.753
My cousin's paying me
$37 a week.

09:14.755 --> 09:17.756
[ Car passing ]

09:20.694 --> 09:22.961
I could
get my own place.

09:22.963 --> 09:25.764
I could live with you.
Be your woman.

09:25.766 --> 09:27.499
Crazy.
You're too young.

09:27.501 --> 09:29.167
Well, I could lie.

09:29.169 --> 09:30.569
Shoot.
The preacher or the justice

09:30.571 --> 09:32.504
gon' want a birth certificate
or something.

09:32.506 --> 09:33.972
Then I'll change it.

09:33.974 --> 09:37.910
You know, I just want to be
with you and get married,

09:37.912 --> 09:40.312
be your woman.

09:40.314 --> 09:43.381
C'mon.
You're dreaming.

09:43.383 --> 09:45.717
You're all I dream about.

09:45.719 --> 09:49.922
♪♪

09:53.928 --> 09:55.794
Smith: What do we got?

09:55.796 --> 09:57.195
Matt: Hey, are you okay?

09:57.197 --> 09:59.932
Has this colored boy
been bothering you?

09:59.934 --> 10:01.866
No, sir.

10:01.868 --> 10:03.936
I'm colored, sir.

10:03.938 --> 10:06.871
[ Conversing indistinctly ]

10:06.873 --> 10:08.741
You're colored?

10:08.743 --> 10:12.744
Yes, sir.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.146
I'm mixed race.

10:14.148 --> 10:15.614
My mother, she's Negro,

10:15.616 --> 10:18.483
and I live with her
over in East Sparks.

10:18.485 --> 10:19.818
Uh-huh.

10:19.820 --> 10:22.621
Hey!

10:22.623 --> 10:24.757
She's colored.

10:24.759 --> 10:26.759
Get out of here.

10:26.761 --> 10:28.493
I said get going.

10:28.495 --> 10:30.462
Get!

10:31.898 --> 10:34.299
♪♪

10:37.972 --> 10:40.905
All right, let's go.

10:40.907 --> 10:42.307
All right, go on home.

10:42.309 --> 10:44.709
Don't be out here with
these boys, messing around.

10:44.711 --> 10:46.711
You got school tomorrow.
Go!

10:46.713 --> 10:51.550
♪♪

10:54.521 --> 10:57.990
♪♪

11:02.863 --> 11:07.633
♪♪

11:11.472 --> 11:13.938
Well...

11:13.940 --> 11:18.010
like Ben Hecht said, kid,
and he was a great writer --

11:18.012 --> 11:20.278
there ain't a profession
out there, not even soldiering,

11:20.280 --> 11:22.414
that makes a selfless hero
like journalism.

11:22.416 --> 11:23.882
Is that right?

11:23.884 --> 11:25.750
Yeah, that's right.

11:25.752 --> 11:28.687
And Duffy said,
"Socially, a journalist

11:28.689 --> 11:31.556
fits between a whore
and a bartender,

11:31.558 --> 11:34.626
but spiritually,
he stands beside Galileo.

11:34.628 --> 11:36.829
He knows
the world is round."

11:36.831 --> 11:38.163
Yeah,<i> eppur si muove.</i>

11:38.165 --> 11:40.032
Whores know that, too.
-But -- But --

11:40.034 --> 11:43.902
But the most important rule
of journalism is this, kid --

11:43.904 --> 11:47.873
never have a hangover
on your own time.

11:52.913 --> 11:54.779
So, how you doing,
Mister Singletary?

11:54.781 --> 11:56.314
You got to give me something,
Pete. I can't --

11:56.316 --> 11:57.650
Oh, come on, Jay.

11:57.652 --> 12:00.052
You know how the<i> Times</i> works.
I do what they tell me.

12:00.054 --> 12:01.453
Just get me something,
otherwise,

12:01.455 --> 12:02.855
I'm gonna kill somebody.

12:02.857 --> 12:04.789
'Cause I try, I put your name
on the byline,

12:04.791 --> 12:06.324
and they shit-can it.
They're elephants.

12:06.326 --> 12:07.926
Give me something, Peter,
or I'm gonna kill myself.

12:07.928 --> 12:09.127
-All right.
-I'll kill myself.

12:09.129 --> 12:10.395
All right, all right,
all right.

12:10.397 --> 12:14.266
All right, I got something.
I got something.

12:14.268 --> 12:16.835
Maybe I got
something in here.

12:19.606 --> 12:22.741
Here. Tomorrow morning at
the city morgue early,

12:22.743 --> 12:24.342
there's a press conference.

12:24.344 --> 12:26.745
Girl got hacked.
Might be interesting.

12:26.747 --> 12:32.417
The cop said the body was,
and I quote, "really something."

12:32.419 --> 12:33.752
Janice Brewster.

12:33.754 --> 12:35.153
Give me some photos.

12:35.155 --> 12:37.155
Write me something real.
I'll see what I can do.

12:37.157 --> 12:39.157
Maybe a little more eloquent
than "really something."

12:39.159 --> 12:41.360
Another stupid little murder
about nothing

12:41.362 --> 12:45.430
that'll change nothing, and...
nobody cares.

12:45.432 --> 12:47.232
You know what? That's the gig.
You above it?

12:47.234 --> 12:48.901
No. I'm down in the gutter
lookin' up at it.

12:48.903 --> 12:50.969
-Great.
-Life Savers.

12:50.971 --> 12:52.304
You mind?
-You're welcome.

12:52.306 --> 12:54.239
I love you.

12:54.241 --> 12:56.174
Do you write for
the<i> L.A. Times?</i>

12:56.176 --> 12:58.310
-Do I what?
-You write for the<i> L.A. Times?</i>

12:58.312 --> 13:01.780
[ Laughs ]

13:01.782 --> 13:03.315
Ohhh, no.

13:03.317 --> 13:06.050
No, no.
I'm a -- I'm a --

13:06.052 --> 13:08.987
I'm a goddamn stringer
for the<i> Examiner.</i>

13:08.989 --> 13:11.389
I'm a loser.

13:11.391 --> 13:13.058
Can you dig it?

13:15.329 --> 13:17.396
You got a problem, hotshot?
-Okay.

13:17.398 --> 13:19.798
No, no problem.

13:19.800 --> 13:21.199
No?
'Cause if you're feeling --

13:21.201 --> 13:22.467
if you're feeling froggy,
we can do this dance.

13:22.469 --> 13:24.469
You just make a jump.
-It's okay.

13:24.471 --> 13:25.604
Pick a lily pad.

13:25.606 --> 13:28.607
[ Crunches loudly ]

13:28.609 --> 13:31.009
You want a Life Saver, kiddo?
-No, thank you.

13:31.011 --> 13:32.611
Want me to drop you off
at school?

13:32.613 --> 13:34.880
It's okay.

13:38.218 --> 13:40.685
Jesus.
What's wrong with him?

13:40.687 --> 13:42.621
What's wrong
with Jay Singletary?

13:42.623 --> 13:46.424
Shit,
where do I even start?

13:46.426 --> 13:49.027
He was a Marine at the Chosin
in Korea for one,

13:49.029 --> 13:51.429
but his problems
are bigger than that, even.

13:51.431 --> 13:53.565
You know when he was 18,
he was a full-time reporter

13:53.567 --> 13:55.433
for the<i> L.A. Times?</i>

13:55.435 --> 13:57.702
He was
a damn good writer.

13:57.704 --> 14:00.372
But he messed up,
you know?

14:00.374 --> 14:02.907
Some stories
you can't tell.

14:02.909 --> 14:04.443
What's that mean?

14:04.445 --> 14:06.044
Well, it means --
and you'll learn this --

14:06.046 --> 14:08.981
some stories
don't want to be told.

14:08.983 --> 14:12.050
Some stories
will eat you alive.

14:12.052 --> 14:15.054
♪♪

14:18.793 --> 14:22.127
♪♪

14:26.933 --> 14:29.168
Well, look what the cat
drug in.

14:31.806 --> 14:34.206
Hi, Mama.

14:37.678 --> 14:39.744
Where you been?

14:39.746 --> 14:41.013
Just at work.

14:41.015 --> 14:43.482
Came straight home.

14:43.484 --> 14:45.517
Is that right?

14:48.955 --> 14:51.290
Hold up.

14:56.630 --> 15:03.235
You was with that
Lewis Ferguson, wasn't you?

15:03.237 --> 15:05.037
Hmm?

15:05.039 --> 15:06.638
Well, let me tell you something,
baby girl.

15:06.640 --> 15:08.841
He ain't no good.

15:08.843 --> 15:10.975
You better than him.

15:10.977 --> 15:13.578
He a loser.
He is no good!

15:13.580 --> 15:17.182
Lewis Ferguson's a good man,
Mama.

15:17.184 --> 15:19.184
I love him,
and he loves me.

15:19.186 --> 15:22.721
Oh, my goodness,
you stupid girl.

15:22.723 --> 15:25.123
You stupid!

15:25.125 --> 15:26.991
Shit.
Stupid girl.

15:26.993 --> 15:28.861
"Oh, I love him.

15:28.863 --> 15:31.296
Oh, my stars."

15:35.335 --> 15:38.871
Need to do better than
this little Podunk town.

15:38.873 --> 15:40.739
Goddamn
Lewis Ferguson?

15:40.741 --> 15:43.208
And how am I supposed
to do better, Mama?

15:43.210 --> 15:45.678
This is where I belong.
This is my home.

15:45.680 --> 15:48.080
Where you belong.

15:48.082 --> 15:51.684
You don't know nothing
where you belong.

15:51.686 --> 15:54.152
Shit.

15:54.154 --> 15:58.290
You belong -- shit.

15:58.292 --> 16:00.092
-Mama...

16:00.094 --> 16:02.294
I saw that
white man again.

16:02.296 --> 16:04.296
The one
I told you about.

16:04.298 --> 16:06.598
Yeah,
I seen him again today.

16:09.436 --> 16:11.503
Why -- Why you worrying
about him, huh?

16:11.505 --> 16:13.438
Worrying about some white man
