39:38.579 --> 39:43.549
♪♪

39:46.720 --> 39:49.922
Jimmy Lee:
You feel that?

39:49.924 --> 39:52.791
I wanted you to feel it --

39:52.793 --> 39:56.795
when God
tears your heart out.

39:56.797 --> 40:00.198
That's what I live with.

40:00.200 --> 40:03.802
And everything can be snatched
away from me at any moment.

40:05.672 --> 40:08.807
When you was a baby,

40:08.809 --> 40:13.579
you had them blond curls.

40:14.615 --> 40:16.681
[ Chuckles ]

40:16.683 --> 40:20.018
We was at the supermarket.

40:20.020 --> 40:22.621
White woman said
she was gonna call the cops.

40:22.623 --> 40:25.591
I had to tell them,
"I'm just watching her."

40:28.428 --> 40:30.629
I was your nanny.

40:30.631 --> 40:32.965
I know, Mama.

40:32.967 --> 40:35.834
♪♪

40:38.505 --> 40:40.572
What the hell you think
you're doing?

40:40.574 --> 40:43.442
-I'm leaving.
-Leaving?

40:43.444 --> 40:45.043
Like --
Like hell you are.

40:45.045 --> 40:48.913
Like hell you ain't.
-I am.

40:48.915 --> 40:50.182
Oh...

40:50.184 --> 40:53.185
Okay, this is about
that Lewis boy, right?

40:53.187 --> 40:54.653
Huh?

40:54.655 --> 40:56.054
I'll call the police.
I'll see him in jail!

40:56.056 --> 40:57.656
No,
I ain't going with Lewis.

40:57.658 --> 41:00.192
I'm going to Los Angeles.

41:00.194 --> 41:01.994
What?

41:01.996 --> 41:03.662
What are you talking about?
What for?

41:03.664 --> 41:05.197
I called him.

41:05.199 --> 41:06.799
You called who?

41:06.801 --> 41:09.101
My grandfather.

41:11.005 --> 41:15.073
You hear that?
-Yeah, I heard you.

41:15.075 --> 41:16.274
I heard you.

41:16.276 --> 41:18.677
Well, he's invited me
to Los Angeles,

41:18.679 --> 41:21.013
and I'm going.

41:21.015 --> 41:23.015
Go on, then.
I always --

41:23.017 --> 41:26.351
I always knew that you'd leave
me, so go on and go.

41:26.353 --> 41:28.487
You had me thinking
you were dead just now.

41:28.489 --> 41:31.156
You know how scared I was?
I ran here from the hospital.

41:31.158 --> 41:32.557
What would I tell
Sister Sarah?

41:32.559 --> 41:35.894
"Oh, yeah, my mama, she ain't
dead. She's just crazy."

41:40.967 --> 41:44.369
You know,
I am leaving, Mama.

41:44.371 --> 41:46.638
I'm going to find
my real family.

41:46.640 --> 41:49.541
♪♪

41:55.782 --> 42:00.319
♪♪

42:07.461 --> 42:09.994
Watch out, man.

42:09.996 --> 42:12.665
Old Billis beat Reginald Hicks
up so bad,

42:12.667 --> 42:16.068
he died at
the 84th Street substation.

42:16.070 --> 42:18.336
Billis on the rough side.

42:18.338 --> 42:20.773
Now you tell me.

42:22.209 --> 42:25.210
-White boys surely do bleed.
-Yeah.

42:25.212 --> 42:27.346
It's pathetic, I know.

42:30.417 --> 42:32.016
Why are you in here?

42:32.018 --> 42:33.418
-Why?
-Yeah.

42:33.420 --> 42:36.088
I expect they'll tell me
at some point.

42:37.758 --> 42:40.559
Why you in here, man?

42:40.561 --> 42:44.763
Why am I here? Uh...

42:44.765 --> 42:46.932
Trying too hard or...

42:49.636 --> 42:53.105
not trying hard enough.

42:53.107 --> 42:55.374
It's hard to tell, Calvin.

43:00.180 --> 43:02.247
Lewis:
That's a long way.

43:02.249 --> 43:04.116
I've never been
to Los Angeles.

43:04.118 --> 43:06.718
It's only for a week.

43:06.720 --> 43:09.088
♪♪

43:12.659 --> 43:17.329
If you find out who you are
and find your rich family,

43:17.331 --> 43:19.664
why would you want
to come back here?

43:19.666 --> 43:22.667
'Cause it doesn't matter
who I am.

43:22.669 --> 43:24.403
I want to be with you.

43:24.405 --> 43:26.739
Man: Load up!

43:28.475 --> 43:30.675
Take care of yourself now,
you hear?

43:30.677 --> 43:34.613
You know I will.

43:34.615 --> 43:36.148
I got to go.

43:40.154 --> 43:42.487
Bye.

43:42.489 --> 43:44.689
Hey. I'll miss you.

43:44.691 --> 43:47.559
I'll miss you.

43:47.561 --> 43:49.995
♪♪

43:56.637 --> 43:59.772
♪♪

44:05.712 --> 44:08.747
♪♪

44:14.588 --> 44:18.323
[ Engine starts ]

44:18.325 --> 44:23.262
♪♪

44:27.267 --> 44:31.337
♪♪

44:34.908 --> 44:38.177
♪♪

44:42.650 --> 44:45.851
Oh, what the hell?
Jay...

44:47.254 --> 44:51.256
-[ Groans ]
-Come on, come on.

44:51.258 --> 44:54.193
Gentle.
Easy, easy, easy.

44:56.396 --> 44:57.529
This is horse shit.

44:57.531 --> 45:00.132
-Oh, yeah, it is.
-You want to press charges?

45:00.134 --> 45:02.167
Uhh...no.

45:04.204 --> 45:06.472
Just want to make sure
I can still play the piano.

45:06.474 --> 45:07.673
What happened?

45:07.675 --> 45:09.274
-Nothing.
-Was it Billis?

45:09.276 --> 45:11.009
If you want, I can take this
to the captain.

45:11.011 --> 45:12.478
-No, no. Thank you, but no.
-For Christ's sakes,

45:12.480 --> 45:14.279
you're a reporter, Jay.
-It's nothing.

45:14.281 --> 45:16.214
-It's nothing?!
-It's not a big thing.

45:16.216 --> 45:17.883
I don't want to make a stink.
Then next thing you know,

45:17.885 --> 45:21.753
I fly down a flight of stairs
and hang myself in a cell.

45:21.755 --> 45:23.355
You know how it goes.

45:23.357 --> 45:26.291
Well, I talked to him
about dropping the charges.

45:26.293 --> 45:30.829
He agreed, seeing as
we served together and all.

45:30.831 --> 45:32.630
Thanks, pal.

45:32.632 --> 45:35.100
Ooh.

45:35.102 --> 45:37.102
[ Laughs ]
-What's that?

45:37.104 --> 45:41.373
Oh, 20 exposures
that Billis did not find.

45:41.375 --> 45:42.441
[ Smooches ]

45:44.444 --> 45:45.711
[ Sighs ]

45:45.713 --> 45:48.514
Listen, Jay...Be careful.

45:48.516 --> 45:50.382
Billis, he's just a hand.

45:50.384 --> 45:52.650
You don't want to see
what he's connected to.

45:52.652 --> 45:53.919
What are you
talking about?

45:53.921 --> 45:55.721
I'm talking about
if you're seeing Billis,

45:55.723 --> 45:57.756
you're in
the wrong place.

45:59.927 --> 46:02.394
Story of my life.
I'll see you around.

46:02.396 --> 46:05.330
1 to 10, how great do I look?
Don't answer that.

46:05.332 --> 46:06.998
You ought to come for dinner
some time.

46:07.000 --> 46:08.466
Two up, one back,
right?

46:08.468 --> 46:09.935
Take the higher ground.

46:09.937 --> 46:13.539
Take the high ground, and don't
piss in the stream, boys.

46:13.541 --> 46:14.940
We'll be drinking
that water tomorrow.

46:14.942 --> 46:16.875
We'll be drinking
that water tomorrow.

46:16.877 --> 46:19.511
♪♪

46:26.353 --> 46:29.188
♪♪

46:35.629 --> 46:37.363
Thank you.

46:37.365 --> 46:40.566
♪♪

46:45.906 --> 46:48.507
♪♪

46:54.648 --> 46:56.515
♪♪

47:03.257 --> 47:05.591
♪♪

47:11.799 --> 47:15.367
♪♪

47:20.540 --> 47:22.474
Beautiful day.

47:22.476 --> 47:25.611
Yes, it is.

47:25.613 --> 47:28.080
-Smoke?
-No, thank you.

47:28.082 --> 47:30.616
I don't smoke.

47:30.618 --> 47:33.018
That's good.

47:35.489 --> 47:37.889
Are you traveling far?
-No, sir.

47:37.891 --> 47:41.026
Just to Los Angeles.

47:41.028 --> 47:44.296
What brings you
to Los Angeles?

47:44.298 --> 47:46.365
A Greyhound.

47:48.502 --> 47:52.304
I'm visiting my grandfather.
Never met him.

47:52.306 --> 47:54.440
Well,
that will be interesting.

47:54.442 --> 47:59.445
Yeah, I just want to know
where I come from and who I am.

47:59.980 --> 48:02.380
[ Bus engine starts ]

48:02.382 --> 48:06.051
That's a good thing
to know.

48:06.053 --> 48:08.120
[ Horn honks ]
-Well, that's my ride.

48:08.122 --> 48:10.656
See ya.
-Bye now.

48:10.658 --> 48:13.459
♪♪

